body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/441\n\n## Problem\n`pm create --help --type Task` prints a \"Type-aware option policies\" block listing 19 flags as \"required\", but a 3-flag create succeeds in default mode. The list is actually type-APPLICABLE flags and ignores the active --create-mode. Agents over-provision creates or judge create unusable.\n\n## Proposed fix\nHelp must reflect the real policy: genuinely mandatory fields for the ACTIVE create-mode (default -> --title/--type), with the full set labeled \"applicable\" (or \"required in strict mode\"). Strict mode shows the strict set.\n\n## Definition of done\nType-aware help output matches runtime enforcement per create-mode; spec covers default vs strict rendering; contracts/help snapshots updated."
